Location.Address: 98 Bath St, Glasgow G2 2EN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
HAND-PULLED NOODLES

This place was amazing! Only had time for a quick lunch but the dishes I tasted were awesome. I got the chicken stir fry and was able to have some of the beef brisket noodle soup.

Both were a good sized portion and very filling. The beef brisket noodles were fantastic. Great deep and rich broth and the meat was lovely and tender.

This place is cash only by the way but there is an ATM close by.

Location.Address: 80 Bath St, Glasgow G2 2EN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
This is exactly what you need from a budget hotel. Very standard services. Good central location. Reasonably priced compared to other hotels and AirBNBs.

For a one or two-night stay, this is exactly what you need which are the bare essentials.

It had a good-sized bed for two people. One criticism is that my room it didn't have a bedside table on one side of the bed. It's understandable because the room probably doesn't have enough space to fit everything.

Would stay again for a day trip to Glasgow!

Location.Address: St James Square, Edinburgh EH1 3AD, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment: The hot chocolate was really good!

Location.Address: 31 Jeffrey St, Edinburgh EH1 1DH, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
WORLD CLASS

Made a booking for 2 people on a Saturday. It wasn't too busy so you could try and walk in. It got quite busy at like 8-9. Top notch service throughout our meal.

We started off with a lobster bisque. There were these very delectable kale chips on top which were nicely crisped and salted. The bisque itself was lovely. It was very creamy and had the most delightful seafood taste running throughout with the occasional morsel of lobster.

Then for the mains I got the Halibut which was awesome! Everything worked so well together on the plate. There were the purees which are always great to add a little more to each other element. You could taste how quality the Halibut was with each bite. My favourite though was the potatoes on the side. It was like a next level mashed potatoes and was really creamy, garlicy, and flavourful.

I tried a litte of the patridge. Loved what was done with the mushrooms and potatoes on that dish.

We ended with the lavender creme brulee which was amazing. It had the necessarily crispy top and was just the right amount of sweet.

Loved my meal here and will definitely  be back as I imagine every dish on the menu is a winner

Location.Address: C. Dr. Ramon Solanich i Riera, 9, 08905 L'Hospitalet de Llobregat, Barcelona, Spain

properties.Review Comment:
SUPERB FOOD WITH FRIENDLY AND COMFORTING EXPERIENCE

Came here twice while on holiday. It such a great experience! It's quite a small place with a handful of tables. From what I could see there was only one lady working there and she was very friendly. The second time we came in she gave us some free coffee and dessert!

The food was amazing. We just got three portions of whatever was being served which was an amazing selection of Ethiopian dishes on some lovely injera. All of the dishes  were full of flavour and worked really well together. It wasn't too spicy but just enough to provide that kick that you need

From what I remember the meal was well priced.

Great break from Spanish cuisine  if you need one.

Location.Address: 55 Bd Mohamed Zerktouni, Marrakech 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment: I came back here a couple of years later and its still very good. The salad selection is actually quite amazing. A lot of smal dishes with huge variety and lots of flavours

Location.Address: J2G6+QWP, Derb Semmarine, Marrakech 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
RICH FILLING FOOD

It was a really great meal! Came here on a weekday for lunch time at around 12. There were tables available to sit down.

There's no menu to look at. We had someone that spoke French fluently so it was easy for us to order.

We got some small plates of fries and salad. We were about to be brought a plate for each of the members of our party. But we thought it would be too much. We should have taken them all because the fries were so crispy and morish. The salad was also great as the freshness was a nice break to cut through the richness of the meat.

We had the lamb tangia and then roast lamb. The lamb tagine was superb. A lovely undertone of lemon ran throughout which was a great addition to the tender lamb. The grilled lamb was spectacular. All the meats were to tender that they were falling all the bone. An extremely delicious and indulgent meal.

For six people the meal came to about £18 which was great value for money

Will be recommending this place to anyone who visits marrakech.

Location.Address: Floor 4, St James Quarter, Edinburgh EH1 3AE, United Kingdom
St James Square, Edinburgh EH1 3AD, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
INDULGENT SUGARY GOODNESS

Came here around 9pm on a bank holiday. It was pretty quiet and we easily got a table for 3 people. One thing I would like to see in Edinburgh is more places that are open late that serve food and its cool to see places like this that are open past 10pm.

We got the 'I Won't Tell If You Won't' which is super heavy. I'm not sure how a single person is meant to finish it and carry on with their day. It was amazingly chocolatey. The crepes were fairly warm and the strawberries weren't as fresh as I would
d have liked. It didn't matter though cause it was drowned out by the rich Belgian milk chocolate sauce.

It was quite late and there weren't that many people so the staff were cleaning up which is why we had to flag down staff at some points to get what we needed.

I enjoyed the dessert I had and the place looked cool. Excited to go back here when I need a sweet treat at the end of the day.

Location.Address: 1 Derb Aarjane, Marrakesh 40000, Morocco
5 Canonmills, Edinburgh EH3 5HA, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
TREMENDOUS PANCAKES

This is one of the only cafes in my area that is open at 8am. It's a cozy and friendly cafe.

The pancakes were some of the best I've had in Edinburgh! They were light and fluffy with the perfect amount of sweetness to them. The berries were a great addition to cut through the sweetness of the pancakes.

I'm definitely coming back here to try out more of what's on offer!

Location.Address: 26 Vinicombe St, Glasgow G12 8BE, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
ALL AROUND AMAZING

Came here on a Saturday afternoon at around opening time with no reservation. The restaurant wasn't busy, so we got a table without any problems for two people. The service was on point and we were checked upon frequently by the staff. The food came out relatively quickly at no cost to the quality of the dishes.

We started with the highly recommended beef skewers which had a beautiful caramelised and smoky outside with a juicy inside. I would 100% get this again when I return. We also got the cucumber salad which was perfectly fresh and flavourful to cut through the saltiness and richness of all the meat dishes.

For the mains, we got the braised beef masaman curry which was spectacular. The curry was sweet and rich with the beef just falling apart with tenderness. The potatoes were a great accompaniment as they had absorbed all the curry goodness.

Every dish that we got was high quality, full of flavours and just amazing!

This was one of the best meals that I've had in Glasgow and I can't wait to go again. I'm looking forward to its opening in Edinburgh soon!

Location.Address: 70 Mitchell St, Glasgow G1 3LX, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
PHENOMENAL PASTA

Easily managed to walk in on a Friday afternoon although soon after it was getting fairly busy. The staff were super efficient and our food came out quickly. It's quite a cool place because from my table I could see the pasta being made and the ravioli being stuffed. I haven't been to a place with such an open kitchen and so it's interesting to see the steps of how your food is made.

We got two dishes which were shared and a plate of bread to scoop up the sauces at the bottom. It was definitely needed cause there is so much flavour in the sauces.

I started off with the Squid ink spaghetti with the monkfish. I could taste the quality and freshness of the pasta in each bite. The fish tasted nice and there was a lovely subtle chilli tomato flavour throughout.

I also had a portion of the mushroom ravioli in a truffle butter sauce. It was an amazingly tasty and filling pasta bathed in the lovely decadent sauce. I still think about the richness of this pasta from time to time.

When I go back to Glasgow I'm coming back here first!

Location.Address: 190 Sussex Gardens, Tyburnia, London W2 1TU, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
DELICIOUS & QUALITY FOOD

It really is a hidden gem tucked away on the corner in Paddington. It's quite a small restaurant so a reservation is most certainly needed. Each of the staff were really friendly and one of the chefs even came to the table to see how our meal went.

To get the range of dim sum, we got both the deep fried platter and the seafood platter. Each piece was beautifully crispy.

I got the beef rendang rolls which were fantastic. Again amazingly crispy with a rich and tender beef filling.

The most enjoyable thing about this place is the variety of dishes that you can get which allow you to experience a lot of different, tasty and fresh flavours. Everything thing including the prawn laksa and nasi lemak ayam were fantastic.

Location.Address: 12-13 St Andrew Square, Edinburgh EH2 2AF, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
FANTASTIC VALUE, FOOD AND SERVICE

Managed to book a table for three people for 7:30 on a Tuesday the day before. It was fairly busy when we arrived so would definitely recommend booking. Amarone had a relaxing environment and a nice decor. The service was great with the waiters checking in every so often and accomodating some extra requests.

The starters were beautiful! The fried mozzarella sticks were indulgent with a lovely crispy coating and a soft cheesy inside. The prawns were perfectly cooked and were bathed in a tasty buttery sauce. I also had the bruschetta which had nice crunchy bread and fresh tomatoes.

I got the rigatoni pasta for mains. The ricotta, sausage, and tomato sauce all melded together to make a luxurious creamy sauce which made each bite extremely morish!

Bread had to be requested for the table so that the sauces from the pasta and starters could be scooped up. Definitely needed because all the sauces were so delicious.

I got the creme brulée for dessert and they made it fantastically with a crispy sweet top and creamy base. Although I probably wouldn't order it again as I'm personally not a fan of the lime tones throughout.

Overall, I had a great meal with great service and I can't wait to go again!

Location.Address: 67 Home St, Edinburgh EH3 9JP, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment: Came back again and it was just as amazing as the first time

Location.Address: 1 Palmerston Pl, Edinburgh EH12 5AF, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
ABSOLUTELY OUTSTANDING

I booked a table for two on a Friday at 6pm. This was one of the only times on that day that was available. After being seated we were given bread which had a lovely crunchy crust and tasted great. The waitress made us feel very welcome and comfortable.

This restaurant does one of my favourite things which is having an ever changing menu depending on the season and ingredients they have in.

To start off, we got the Mackerel with a caper remoulade. The fish was so fresh and delicate with a beautiful subtle salty taste. The creamy remoulade was also fresh and crunchy, and thus paired excellently with the slices of fish.

Following that, I got the Jacobs sheep which was amazing! The meat was so juicy and tender. Every bite was succulent and satisfying. There was a nice accompaniment of chickpeas and greens which were perfectly cooked. Everything lay upon a beautiful sweet and slightly spicy jus. At the end of the meal I got some more bread just to soak up every bit that was left.

I also got to try the braised beef shins which were practically falling apart because it was so succulent. Beautiful creamy mashed potatoes on the side as well.

Finally we got the chocolate mousse for dessert which was nice but I wouldn't come back for it.

Overall it was amazing and very memorable. Literally making my mouth water thinking about having it again soon.

Location.Address: 56 Broughton St, Edinburgh EH1 3SA, United Kingdom
Location.Business Name: L'Escargot Bleu Restaurant and Wine Bar

properties.Review Comment:
PHENOMENAL FOOD

I came here on a Friday evening with a table booked for two people at 7:30pm. Service was welcoming and they did this cool thing where they brought the menu to us on a blackboard. It's written on a black board because it changes daily. Server came round to explain the specials and then take our order.

I started off with the crab soup. I've never had it before but it was lovely. It had a nice sweet oceanic flavour throughout. I have to say that it had more of a brothy texture than a soupy one. One of the best things about the soup was the side of rouille! Amazing deep and strong flavours from the garlic.

Then I got the Braised Beef Cheeks which were fantastic. Extremely juicy and so tender that they were practically falling apart. The sauce had a lovely sweetness to it and it was so good that after the meal I scooped up the rest with some of the bread provided. I also loved having the shallots as they had soaked up all of the rich flavours from the sauce.

I can't wait to come back here to see more dishes and try new things.

Location.Address: 20 Princes St, Edinburgh EH2 2AN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING QUALITY AND VERY DELICIOUS

I've come here twice and both times were fantastic! The staff are very warm, friendly and helpful.

I've gotten the soup both times and both times they were delightful. Very flavorful and wholesome. There was also some decent bread served up with it.

First time I came here, I got one of the sharing boards and it was awesome! Everything on the platter was so superb and delectable. The steak was perfectly cooked and tender. The ribs were meaty with a lovely sweet BBQ sauce on top. The prawns had a great grilled taste to them. Lovely crispy chips the first time around. If you order this you'll need to go with a big appetite just so that you can eat everything because I think you'll definitely want to.

Next time round I got the steak frites from the lunch menu. Fries this time round weren't as crispy as the first time round but were still very nice. The steak pieces were fantastic again. Perfectly cooked and extremely moreish.

I highly recommend going here!

Location.Address: 332 Kilburn High Rd, London NW6 2QN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment: Fantastic meal again at wingmans!

Location.Address: 6 Queensferry St, Edinburgh EH2 4PA, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
TASTY SUSHI

Came here on a Wednesday evening at around 7pm with a reservation for 2. It was quite busy and so the reservation was definitely needed. All the staff were nice and the service was rapid.

It's a cool looking restaurant and I liked that they had an anime theme within it.

To start, I got the prawn gyoza which were solid. It had a satisfying bite to it and decent texture to the wrap. There was a lovely flavour of soy sauce running over all the gyoza.

Then I moved on to the best part of the meal which was the sushi. Each piece was great as they had a fulfilling mouth feel and fresh taste. I thoroughly enjoyed the eel as it had an amazing sweet smokey taste in every bite. I loved the wasabi as well. It had a wonderful sharp heat that  paired well with the soothing tastes of the sushi.

If I go back I will definitely order twice as much sushi instead of the chicken ramen or chicken donburi. I personally wasn't a fan of either of those dishes as the ramen was closer to a chicken soup and then donburi was a little bland for me. On the other hand the miso soup was too salty for my tastes.

Sushi was lovely and I look forward to getting a bigger platter!

Location.Address: 21-25 Duke St, Leith, Edinburgh EH6 8HH, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT BURGERS

Came here on a Thursday evening with a booking for three people. The staff were really friendly and were quick to take our orders and bring them out.

I got the G-Funk burger. Really good! The pattie was cooked to perfection. The bun was good quality and the burger was the right size. I immensely enjoyed the BBQ sauce within which gave a great sweet flavour throughout.

The picante fries were great as well, having a great crisp and hint of spice to it.

Nice place to grab a burger, fries and a drink.

Location.Address: 58 Dalkeith Rd, Edinburgh EH16 5AD, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
EXCELLENT SUNDAY ROAST

Came here with a reservation for four people on Sunday at 4:30. Even though we arrived a little early the staff were nice enough to accommodate us. Whilst we were there, they were busy so we had to flag down the staff a couple of times or we would have been waiting a while. I would say that the service could be a little better if they came by more often to check and follow up.

I got the soup of the day for starters which was tomato soup and it was splendid. Packed with flavour and had great consistency.

Following that I got the roast which was awesome. The beef was succulent and delicious. All the trimmings were excellent including the sauteed greens and the roast potatoes were spectacular. Really crisp on the outside and fluffy on the inside. I could have had 20 of them.

It would have been ideal to have a little pot of gravy to pour.

Then for dessert I got the crème brûlée which had a lovely light vanilla flavour that balanced out quite nicely with the rich cream.

It was a really great meal and I look forward to coming back after a hike up Arthur's seat!

Location.Address: 78, Commercial Quay, Leith, Edinburgh EH6 6LX, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
SUPREME DINING EXPERIENCE

I was gifted the set lunch menu for two here and was able to book two days beforehand. The whole calendar looked full for a while so I wasn't sure if I just got lucky or if they release a couple of tables closer to the actual date. I got a table for 12:15 on a Thursday. The staff throughout the meal were attentive and considerate. Everytime a dish was placed on the table, the server gave a concise description of the dish, listing each ingredient. It's nice to have some context of the meal and to see the kitchin's philosophy of nature to plate become apparent.

One thing that I enjoyed immensely were the small dishes given, starting off with a mini seafood quiche which tasted fresh and salty. Then the bread and butter was given out which just had that high quality feel and taste about it. To top it all off there was a little portion of pea soup which had some intense flavours.

For starters I had the Ox which had bone broth marmalade along with some petite legume farcis. All these dishes really bring out the tasty flavours of the vegetables. The bone broth marmalade was really cool to try.

Then I had the Pithivier of Roe Deer as my main. This was amazing and had a great meaty flavour packed within.

To finish off I had the Chocolate pannacotta. The sweetness of the chocolate and the taste of the berries within balanced nicely. The bay leave ice cream on the side was fantastic as well.

Everything in the meal was portioned extremely well and my appetite was completely satiated at the end of the meal. The highest quality ingredients were used and you could really tell that you were getting the best at every stage of the meal.

Location.Address: St James Square, Quarter, Edinburgh EH1 3AD, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
TREMENDOUS RAMEN

I ate lunch here three days in a row because the ramen was just so good and I also enjoy going to St James Quarter. There was a little bit of a wait each time but there was always a table available.
The service is incredibly quick and very friendly.

The Black Tonkatsu Ramen is phenomenal. The broth is rich, salty and has a great subtle taste of garlic running throughout the dish. There are usually three juicy pieces of chashu that are in it which are nice and fatty. I love that there are whole bits of garlic in the broth. It really adds to the flavour and makes you wanna finish all the broth which I did each time.

I also got the hell ramen and really enjoyed that as well. It has a great heat which is not overwhelming and combines fantastically with the taste of the broth.

Green tea was lovely.

I have been multiple times and plan on going back again soon.

Location.Address: 5 Bernard St, Leith, Edinburgh EH6 6PW, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
DELICIOUS CROISSANTS

At the time of writing this, you could only get croissants for take away but I can imagine that you'll soon be able to sit in.

The Strawberry & Cream one was amazing. It was perfectly filled and every bite was a treat.

All the sweet croissants are awesome! They are all tender and flaky on the outside and have a soft swirl of pastry and air on the inside. They are also not overpowered with the sweet fillings or coatings. You can really enjoy everything as it's perfectly balanced. I enjoyed all of them a lot but I would rank them as follows:

1. Strawberries & Cream
2. Raspberry & White Chocolate
3. Chocolate Nutella
4. Almond

I also got the Chicken & Pesto savoury croissant, which was just as good as the sweet. Maybe even better but it could possibly just be my love of pesto talking.

All in all, you definitely need to get some croissants from here.

Location.Address: 6-8 Clerk St, Newington, Edinburgh EH8 9HX, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
TASTY DOSA, STARTERS AND CURRY

Managed to get a table here for around 6pm on a Saturday night for three people. This is a cash only establishment but there is an cash machine across the road.

Our server was great and she walked us through the menu giving us suggestions on what to order and what would be the best sharing dishes.

To start, we got the potato bonda which was amazing. It had great flavour and paired very well with the sauce that it came with.

The chicken masala dosai was pretty good but I was looking for some stronger flavours.

The parotta was great with the chicken Karaikudi but again was also looking for some stronger flavours.

Location.Address: 24 Deanhaugh St, Stockbridge, Edinburgh EH4 1LY, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT SUSHI AND VALUE

This is a cash only place which is mentioned on Google and there is a sign at the front of the restaurant. There's an RBS round the corner to withdraw cash from if you need to.

We ate here on a Sunday at 2:15 and managed to get a table for three people. It was fairly busy but there were some tables free. The table we got was a little weird as it was in the corner and not easy to get in and out of but once you're sitting you can get comfortable.

I got the grilled Eel sushi which tasted amazing and hit all the right flavours. It was soft, tasty and subtly sweet.

I also got the Mixed Bento Box which is good value. Loved having miso soup to accompany it. There was a range of meats in the box which included some lovely duck which was tender and fatty, chicken yakitori and two pieces of sushi which were salmon and tuna. All very delectable.

Location.Address: 162 Ferry Rd., Edinburgh EH6 4NX, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment: Chicken Kati Roll

Location.Address: 162 Ferry Rd., Edinburgh EH6 4NX, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
FANTASTIC & DELICIOUS

Sabzi's is an amazing restaurant that has a great aesthetic! I love the way empty ghee pots are reused as cutlery holders.

My favourite thing about Sabzi is that their menu changes weekly! All the dishes I've had have been outstanding. Really strong flavours and super tasty, and the dishes are carefully put together with high quality ingredients.

The best dishes I've had are the halva, the chickpea curry, the chicken rolls, and the lamb biriyani.

I try and go every weekend because I don't want to miss out on any dishes.

Location.Address: 1 Summerhall Pl, Newington, Edinburgh EH9 1PL, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
BEST ESCAPE ROOM EVER

We managed to book The Distillery escape room for 5 people for 7pm on a Saturday. We were greeted promptly at 7 by our guide Jackie who was super nice. She gave us tons of background information and answered all our questions.

She led us to the room and set the scene for us fantastically.

The puzzles were amazingly designed. Very logical and clever. Clues were given at appropriate moments and Jackie was very supportive of our success. There was a great sense of achievement that was gained throughout the room and everyone in our group had tons of fun.

We did the easy one and the next two rooms that are offered, are more difficult but are meant to be highly rated so I'm 💯% coming back to do them.

Would recommend!!!

Location.Address: Units 3 & 4, Omni Centre, Edinburgh EH1 3AU, United Kingdom
9 Albert Pl, Edinburgh EH7 5HN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING RAMEN

I've been here a couple of times and it's really easy to make a reservation here.

The front of house server is accomodating and really friendly. They were quick to take my order and get the food out

Recently for starters I got the Dumplings! I enjoyed the Kaffir Lime Broth that the dumplings were in as it was rich and creamy. I also got the Wagyu Beef Slider.

The ramen is awesome. Seriously really rich and tasty broth. You can taste the quality in the noodles, ingredients, and meat. I would recommend getting level one heat for the ramen to cut through some of the richness of the broth.

Really great place with a cool vibe and I will definitely come back here!

Location.Address: 13 Antigua St, Edinburgh EH1 3NH, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
PHENOMENAL RICH AND TASTY FOOD

Was able to make a reservation for three people on a Monday for the evening. One of the servers at the front was quick to take us to our seats. You order through your phone by scanning a QR code and it worked fine enough.

Everything was delicious, rich and full of flavour.

I started off with the Philiy Cheesesteak. The tiger roll was nice and soft just allowing you to enjoy the filling. The steak pieces had a great taste and I just wish the sandwich had more of it. The cheese brought the whole thing together.

The buffalo wings were great. They honestly had that authentic North American taste and were extremely moreish.

Finally, I really enjoyed the poutine as it was everything I ever wanted in a poutine. It had the legit cheese curds and gravy covering everything.

Loved this place and excited to go back to try more of their food.

Location.Address: 21 Hawthornvale, Newhaven, Edinburgh EH6 4JT, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT CAFE FOR CHILLING

Came here at around 10am on a Saturday for breakfast and there was a full table available inside. There were quite a few available outside as well. The QR code for the table worked perfectly and it's very easy to order your food.

The service was rapid with everything coming out within minutes of the order being placed.

I got the Chorizo breakfast. The chorizo is amazing and the richness of the meat is balanced nicely with the sweet spicy flavours coming from it as well.

I always enjoy coming here and checking out the pastry selections as well.

Location.Address: 35 Great Jct St, Edinburgh EH6 5HX, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
FANTASTIC BARBERS

Amazingly nice people that give you a warm welcome. I was able to get a haircut here on Monday at around lunch time without a booking.

The barber I had was great to talk to and he was good at helping me figure out what I needed since I'd never had hair as long as what I have now.

Would definitely recommend getting a haircut here!

Location.Address: 23-24 Sandport Pl, Leith, Edinburgh EH6 6EW, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT AND LIVELY ATMOSPHERE ALONG WITH SOME GOOD FOOD

Was able to book a table for 3 people for 8pm on a Tuesday, on the same day with no problems.

All the servers were super nice and welcoming. Service is quick and they're considerate enough to give a detailed run down of the menu when I asked.

When I go back I'm definitely ordering the Mac and cheese starter. The cheese sauce was perfect, packed with flavour and not to heavy which makes all the difference for me.

The Kraken Tacos were really good as well. I think I'd hold off on ordering then again due to the price (and just order more Mac and cheese). But the  flavours of the squid and pesto worked really well together.

I got the burger for mains and it was a good filling burger. The chips were awesome though. They're the great crispy kind of chips.

Would definitely recommend going here for a great pub visit!

Location.Address: Alby's, 8 Portland Terrace, Edinburgh EH6 6LA, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
BEST SANDWICHES EVER

I love albys! It serves some of the best sandwiches. The cool thing about this place is that the sandwiches change every couple of weeks so it's exciting to see whats coming out next. They also change up the sides as well.

One of the best sandwiches that came from albys imo was the Chicken Katsu Sandwich! The chicken was perfectly crispy and the sauce was just perfect.

However, all the ingredients are high quality and you can really taste that extra bit. The bread used for the sandwiches are amazing as well.

If you manage to get to eat inside you'll see that all the staff are super nice and accommodating.

I grab sandwiches from here all the time so I highly recommend doing the same!

DECENT FOOD WITH GREAT SERVICE

First thing to say is that the service here is very good. The staff were super friendly and offered great suggestions for starters and mains.

The food here was pretty good. I got the houmous which was quality cause it tasted perfectly. I'd probably skip out on the Moroccan meatballs next time though. Didn't really standout.

For mains I got the chill gosht kebab. It was a decent sized portion. Not to chilli and was very tender and tasty meat. The okra was a nice side dish as well.

The shisha part of the restaurant wasn't as good though. The staff never refilled our coals and it was a little difficult to get there attention. The shisha itself was fairly decent but would have been way better with consistent replenishments of coal.
properties.Comment: No location information is available for this review

properties.Draft Review Comment:
GREAT TASTING FOOD

Came here on Friday at around 12:30. Managed to get a table for 2 but it was the only one left so it looks like it can get quite busy.

Amazing

Location.Address: 19 N Fort St, Edinburgh EH6 4HB, United Kingdom
9 Victoria St, Edinburgh EH1 2HE, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT FISH AND CHIPS

Came here on a Monday Evening and had reserved a table for 8 people. It wasn't too busy and there were tables around free so you could probably walk in around that time.

Started off getting the Haggis Spring Rolls because they seemed interesting. They were nice and crispy. The Haggis filling was quite good as well. It was good to try but I won't order this one again.

The battered Haddock was classically tasty and hit the spot. It had a nice crispy skin. The chips were thick, crunchy and plentiful.

The dessert platter was okay but I probably wouldn't order this again. Everything was a little to sweet.

Everything was solid but I would probably order a different starter and dessert. Would definitely go back to get some proper fish and chips though!

Location.Address: Mehringdamm 32, 10961 Berlin, Germany

properties.Review Comment:
BEST DONER THAT I'VE HAD IN A WHILE

Came here on a Sunday afternoon at around 3. People aren't kidding about the queue. It looks quite long but it moves pretty fast. All together I probably waited about 20-25 minutes but it was completely worth it.

They're were only 3 options which I kinda like in a menu because that means that they probably do those three options really well. They had the chicken doner kebab, the vegetarian kebab, and the chicken kebab wrap. I got the chicken doner kebab and the wrap.

Both come to 9.80 euros which is decently priced for what you get.

The bread of the chicken doner is crispy and light. The meat is tender and flavorful. The vegetables really add a lot of textures and a sweetness to the doner. And the sauce and cheese ties it all together quite nicely.

Its hard to say which one is get again because I'd both of them again. If I had to choose I'd get the doner kebab because of the bread but the wrap is definitely easier to eat.

Location.Address: Bernauer Str. 63-64, 13355 Berlin, Germany
59 Great Jct St, Edinburgh EH6 5HX, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
TOP QUALITY ITALIAN FOOD

Came here on Monday at around 12:30 and there was one table left. The others were occupied as well as the high side table.

The sever is friendly and took our orders quickly.

We got the GNOCCHI DI PATATE AI FUNGHI pasta and the COURGETTES pizza for lunch.

The great thing about the pizza is that it's pizza base is light allowing you to taste the fresh tomato sauce and toppings. There's a nice spice with this one. It doesn't leave you feeling lethargic  whilst filling you up.

The gnocchi was really good. The sauce was perfectly creamy and there was a lot of it. The mushrooms melded in nicely with the gnocchi.

Really great little Italian place and have come back here and will continue to do so.

Location.Address: 95 Union St, Glasgow G1 3TA, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT EXPERIENCE, FUN AND VALUE

This place is located quite centrally and its right next to the station. So perfect if you want to spend the day in central.

Right from the start our instructor Aaron was energetic, friendly and super welcoming. He was thorough with the safety instructions.

He was great as introducing our group to new throws and giving us competitions.

Aaron really made the axe throwing experience super fun.

The facilities are really good as well. There weren't many people in our booking slot so we were almost able to get our own lanes.

Super fun experience and will definitely go back if I find myself in Glasgow again!

Location.Address: Waxhouse Gate, St Albans AL3 4EW, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
EVERYTHING WAS SUPERB AND AMAZING QUALITY!

Made a reservation for this place for a Wednesday evening. Not sure but feel like its probably unlikely to get a table from just walking in.

The table ordered the Hunter's Linguine, South Coast devilled sprats and Roasted beetroot and Wobbly Bottom goat’s cheese salad. The sprats had a great crispy texture and retained their flavours. I didn't try the salad. The hunters linguine was fantastic. It was creamy, tasty, and the hare was awesome.

I had the steak frites for main and it provided  everything you could ask for in a steak and fries meal. Very satisfying to eat as the steak was juicy.

For dessert, I got the creme brulee and that was perfect as well.

You can't fault this place and I can't wait to go here again!

Location.Address: 66 Joel St, Northwood HA6 1LL, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
DECENT FOOD AND SERVICE

Got here on a Tuesday evening and managed to find parking outside the place. We got a table in the outdoor section. It wasn't busy at all so we easily managed to get a seat.

The shisha was fairly good and cost the standard London prices. We got the Cuban mojito. It was nice to get the standard shisha in all aspects including taste and strength.

The food was the best part of the place. The mixed grill was amazing. Everything had a great spice, flavour and texture to it. It was succulent and good quality. The chilli paneer was also at the same quality.

The only thing I would say that wasn't as good as it could be was the service. The food came out quickly and our order was taken pretty quickly.  However a lot of the time, we had to track down a server to either replace our coals, order more drinks or move inside.

That being said will definitely come back for the food!

Location.Address: 19 Grassmarket, Edinburgh EH1 2HS, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZINGLY TASTY AND UNIQUE ICE CREAM

This is highly recommended to me by a lot of people and for good reason.

So right off the bat you're given a range of different flavours to choose from. On the particular day that I went you were able to choose Olive oil and Oregano flavoured ice cream which I of course I had to try due to how strange it sounded. It was tasted weird at first but grew on me with each spoonful. There was a definite subtle olive taste throughout which was pleasantly welcomed each time I tasted it. It was quite good but I will probably won't order it a second time round.

I went on a Sunday at around 3:30 and there was a handful of people in the queue so was waiting for around 15 minutes

Its reasonably priced and I will definitely come back again!

Location.Address: 56-58 St Mary's St, Edinburgh EH1 1SX, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
FANTASTIC FOOD AND SERVICE

We were able to get a table on a Saturday night at around 7:30. I feel that this place would usually be busy, however there were a few cancellations of reservations this night.

Firstly, everyone that was working here was friendly and ready to help. They gave great recommendations and were overall fantastic at getting the table what we needed.

I was able to try multiple starters which were the homemade humous, the gnocchi, and the kofta. All of them are solid choices however the kofta was pretty amazing and they had a banana chutney that I've never had before but added a nice sweetness to the dish.

I got the courgette wraps for mains. The dish is truly made with the pesto and beetroot chickpea purée. You definitely need one or the other in each bite to carry the dish. Also highly recommend if you love some potato.

Ordered the desert to share for two people which had a range. All of them were good. Probably would have ordered the apple tart by it self because that was the best for me.

Really good!

properties.Draft Review Comment:
CLASSICALLY GOOD PIZZA WITH GREAT SERVICE

Arrived here on

Location.Address: 16 Nicolson St, Edinburgh EH8 9DH, United Kingdom
9F Holyrood Rd, Edinburgh EH8 8FQ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
DESSERTS THAT HITS THE SPOT

It was extremely quiet for a Sunday evening which was actually a great thing. Was able to get served immediately. Never seen so many deliveroo drivers congregating in the same area.

Got the waffle which tasted fairly sweet but was quite thick and heavy. Personally, I needed to share this with someone to finish the waffle. The waffle was a decent base for the ice cream, toppings and sauce. Highly recommend the salted caramel ice cream.

What's great about this place is the vast selection of different ice cream, the various cakes and pastries, the smorgasbord of different toppings, and the decent prices. Its awesome that you can personalize your dessert to quite a high degree.

It's a great place if you need a big hit of sugar and just sugar!

Location.Address: 192 Morrison Street EH3, 192 Morrison St, EH3, Edinburgh EH3 8EB, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING PIZZA, CHEAP DRINKS, AND GREAT STAFF

Got here on a Thursday night at around 6:45 pm and there was quite a lot of tables available.

Had to get their signature froth and flame pizza and it was amazing! The tomato sauce is strong and flavourful. The basils fresh and the all the toppings worked so well together.

They have some really great cocktails such as the espresso martini and the charismatic alchemist.

The service was great as well. Staff were super friendly and helpful with drink orders. The pizza came really quickly.

Would highly recommend going here. It is criminally underated. Definitely deserves to be busy!

Location.Address: 101 Hanover St, Edinburgh EH2 1DJ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
BEST WAFFLES IN EDINBURGH

Came here on a Saturday morning the day after valentine's Day at 11am and it was packed with a line out the door! Didn't wanna wait that long so came back to the place around 11:45 and only had to wait about 10 mins to get a table.

The service here is really friendly and accommodating. they really make sure that you are acknowledged and give you a realistic time of when you will get a seat.

I got the recommended waffles with strawberries, bacon and maple syrup and I got to say that these were some of the best waffles I've had. Everything worked so well together. The taste of the strawberries, sweetness of the syrup and saltiness of the bacon all balanced each other out so nicely and nothing was too overpowering.

The waffles were also light and fluffy! I didn't have that lethargy after eating which is a sign of a great meal.

If you get a chance to go here for breakfast, you must do it!

Location.Address: 31 Crighton Pl, Edinburgh EH7 4NY, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
FANTASTIC SUSHI TO SHARE

Came here at 4pm on a Saturday as it was opening and obviously the whole place was empty so easy to get seats. Make sure to bring cash as they don't take card here.

Started with the Hell Pork Ramen which fairly good. It has a creamy taste however the flavours from the meat don't come through in the broth. I thought it would be spicier but there was only a mild spice from it. Still a good ramen to fulfill any need for ramen.

The sushi Tempura set was amazing. The whole set was quite filling and it was put together fantastically. It tasted perfectly but the most important thing was that the textures were very pleasant.

The sushi is of course quite expensive which is why I begin saying that you should most definitely come in a group so you can share a set and save on costs.

Would come again!

Location.Address: 1-3 Grove St, Edinburgh EH3 8AF, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING FOOD WITH STRONG FLAVOURS

Came here on a Tuesday evening at 6:30 and was easily able to get a table for three people. Although it got quite busy so would recommend making a reservation to be on the safe side.

The service was friendly and the food came out relatively quickly.

The pho with Beef balls was fantastic. It closely resembled pho that I had in Vietnam. The beef slices were tasty, tender and went great with the broth.

The starters were good however I wouldn't order the fresh spring rolls with prawn and chicken as there wasn't much of a meat filling within it. Would definitely order the Special Salad again as that was perfect.

The Pak Choi with garlic had a strong taste but it was amazing.

Would definitely go again! It is a little pricey but definitely worth it.

Location.Address: 30 Grindlay St, Edinburgh EH3 9AP, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT CHOICE AND TASTE FOR THE PRICE

We were easily able to get a booth for three people at around 6:30 on a Wednesday night. It wasn't too busy on that weekday evening.

The service was very efficient. Almost everyone I got up to get another plate of food, my previously used plate was already taken.

The best way I can describe the food is that it was like having takeaway Chinese food but being allowed to have as much as you want.

Everything tasted rather good and exactly what you expect from the dishes you choose.

The reason I would go back here, would be that it's great quality for quite a reasonable price. It's buffet food at the end of the day so go in with reasonable expectations.

Location.Address: 1 Festival Square, Edinburgh EH3 9SR, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT DESSERTS AND SERVICE

Came here two nights in a row in the evening at around 8pm. There's quite a relaxed vibe in this place as we just walked in and were casually able to take a seat.

The waiter was a really nice guy and was quick with  taking our order and serving food.

Not sure if they change up the menu, but the desserts we got were really good. We got the apple tart which was nice. It had a great balance of flavours as the sweetness was balanced with the taste of the apple.

Then we got the chocolate pistachio pot dessert which was pretty good. This one definitely needs to be shared because there is so much sugary goodness in this dish from the ice cream, to the cream, to the chocolate within the pot. The pistachios were a nice touch as they gave the dish some crunch.

For desserts from a hotel restaurant on the weekday, they were pretty good.

Location.Address: 90-92 Lothian Rd, Edinburgh EH3 9BE, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
DECENT BURGERS AND YOU CAN GET POUTINE!

Came here at 6:30 and was able to get a table for two. The table was a little too close to the next table and so it felt a little crowded but not a huge deal.

I got the Royale with Cheese burger which was pretty good but it didn't quite reach the level that I thought it would be at. It was still a decent burger but it wasn't thick enough to give a good bite to the burger. If I go again I will definitely get a different burger with a thicker burger patty.

The other person in my party got the pulled lamb burger which tasted really good!

The grilled chicken poutine was great as well. However the chicken was a little dry on the inside so I would probably order a different variety of poutine next time as well.

Overall it was good but it didn't live up to the hype for me. I might have just ordered things that I didn't personally like so next time I go, I will definitely try some others.

Location.Address: 7 E Market St, Edinburgh EH1 1DH, United Kingdom
142 Renfield St, Glasgow G2 3AU, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT ATMOSPHERE WITH GOOD FOOD

Was taken here on a Friday evening a couple days after new years. Arrived at around 7:30pm and there were a lot of tables available. Started getting a lot busier later on.

I got the Colonel Chipotle burger which was recommended by one of the staff. It came with chips and coleslaw. Both were great quality and very more-ish. The burger was pretty good but honestly I like the sides a lot more. The burger patty was a little to thick for me. Still tasted great!

The atmosphere is probably the best part of this place. It's in the sweet spot where it wasn't too busy or too quiet.

They're also looked like there was a lot of events going on which I need to go back for!

Would recommend going here if you're looking for a place with a decent meal and great atmosphere.

Location.Address: 31-33 Nicolson Square, Edinburgh EH8 9BX, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
CLASSICALLY GREAT TASTING CURRY

Came here on a Wednesday at around 2pm and there were plenty of seats available. It was also new year's Day so was thankful that it was open. About 30 minutes later it got quite busy.

You are able to sit wherever as it setup with communal style seating. There are long tables with plenty of seats around.

At the back of the restaurant is the place to choose and collect your food. It's served canteen style and you're able to see exactly what you're getting.

I got the pilau rice, the chicken curry, the vegetable curry, and the samosas. They are very generous with the portions when dishing out the food.

The best thing about the food for me was that it tastes rich and familiar. Everything tastes exactly like it should and all the dishes work well together which means you could go back and have a completely different combination of dishes.

Lovely comfort food which I will be going back for!

Location.Address: Unit 15, Central Cross, 16-18 Newport Pl, London WC2H 7PR, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
SUPERB FOOD WITH A GREAT UNDERLYING SPICE

Queues started to form for this place just after we arrived at around 5:30pm on Boxing Day.  We were able to be seated immediately but groups definitely had to wait a little if they arrived after 6pm.

The service isn't bad at this place and the food came out quickly. You may however need to be a tad assertive and grab a waiters attention to order your food which is no big deal and a common theme when dining in Chinatown.

All the dishes ordered were great quality and delicious. We started off with the classic peking aromatic duck with pancakes. Everything about it  was spot on!

Afterwards, our main dishes arrived, consisting of egg fried rice, morning glory, crispy shredded beef, the cauliflower dry hot pot, and the salt and pepper prawns.

The rice was perfect and tasted fresh. The morning glory was as expected. The beef and prawns were amazing as well, as they were full of flavour and had a lovely spiciness with every bite.

The best part was the cauliflower dry hot pot which was a new one for me and it tasted great. A lot of different flavours and spices in the pot with perfectly cooked cauliflower.

Would definitely come back!

Location.Address: 87 Queen's Rd, Watford WD17 2QN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
BEST BOARD GAME CAFE EVER

I come here occasionally and usually there's a table free but at peak times like a Friday or Saturday night you need to book. Also be aware that sometimes there are events on in the evening which takes up a section of the place.

The service here is amazing! All the staff are super friendly and willing to help and give you recommendations for board games. If the staff knows how to play a game they'll also help you with the rules.

They have a great selection of board games! If you have no idea what to play there's a helpful board game menu to help with suggestions based on how many people are in your group.

They also serve food and drinks. Everything I've ordered has been decent quality and good value for money.

Genuinely such a great place that you could spend hours at! 🔥

Location.Address: 67 Home St, Edinburgh EH3 9JP, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
COZY CAFE WITH A BEAUTIFUL SELECTION

This was a lovely cafe with a great selection of pastries. The barista was so friendly as well and made sure we were taken care of.

My flat white was perfect. There were a lot of drinks on offer that I will definitely go back to try.

I also got a saffron and rose cake which was light and tasty. Would definitely have it again. Again there was so much to choose from that I'll definitely come back to this place.

Location.Address: 49 Bread St, Edinburgh EH3 9AH, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING PLACE FOR DRINKS

Came here on a Saturday night and it was pretty quiet. I have no idea why it was though because this place was great!

The espresso martini was awesome and it has a little something to do with the fact that it also comes with a small portion of ice-cream!

The service was great and the server recommend an amazing drink which was the banana colada. Such a dangerous drink because it's tasty and so easy to drink.

We were also given little snacks 😍

Come here if you want high quality and tasty drinks!

Location.Address: 97-101 Fountainbridge, Edinburgh EH3 9QG, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT RAMEN IN A GREAT PLACE

It wasn't busy at all for lunch on a Tuesday and there were more than enough seats available at that time. I've been to other branches of this restaurant but this is my favourite one just because of how much space this one has. Also if you sit at the counter you can actually see the chef preparing different dishes which is interesting to see.

The other good thing about this place is that you know that you'll be getting decent ramen. The broth is full of flavour and I would happily have it by itself. The pork is always tender and more-ish.

I tried the pumpkin croquettes which were fantastic.

Would 💯 % come back here!

Location.Address: 208 Bruntsfield Pl, Edinburgh EH10 4DE, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT STEAK

The service here is great. The staff are attentive and friendly. The food came relatively quickly even with having around 16 people in our party.

I got the soup of the day which was a broccoli soup. It was decent but in my opinion, it could have been stronger.

I alsogot the steak from the Christmas menu which was amazing! It was tender, tasty, and cooked perfectly for me. The chips that came along with it were not the best though.

Overall it was a solid meal but a bit pricy for me to go again!

Location.Address: 67 Nicolson St, Newington, Edinburgh EH8 9BZ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
PERFECT COMFORT FOOD

Arrived here on a Tuesday evening at around 7 and it was packed but I managed to grab a table for two. (Tip - front door doesn't fully close so if it's cold the breeze will get you).

The place itself has a nice atmosphere, cute decor, and friendly service. The food came out rapidly! The prices are really reasonable. The shared platter for two was around £20 and you get a good amount of food, dessert , and a drink.

The shared platter was great. Every curry was superb and I wanted a whole lot more . The keema Sheena was v more-ish and might just order a whole dish of that.

Would definitely come back here!

properties.Draft Review Comment:
GREAT PLACE FOR COFFEE

The barista here was super nice

Location.Address: 58 Home St, Edinburgh EH3 9NA, United Kingdom
60 Home St, Edinburgh EH3 9NA, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
EXCELLENT QUALITY DISHES

Managed to grab at table here at around 12:30 on a Sunday. It started to get busy as the lunch crowd rolled in.

Service was great and all the servers were friendly. Food was delivered quickly as well.

We got the crispy diced chicken in spices and egg fried rice which was great! The chicken was decently crisp and had a nice spice to it. The egg fried rice was class.

Also got the Rainbow dumplings which were cool but there were some that I wasn't a hug fan of. The ones I liked were great though! Need to go back to identify which ones they were 🤣

Location.Address: 30 Elm Row, Edinburgh EH7 4AH, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING CURRY FOR THE PRICE

This place strikes me more as a takeaway place however it's very nice to sit in as well. Came for dinner at around 8pm on a Saturday and there were plenty of tables available.

I got the meal deal for 1, which includes 4 pakoras, some poppadoms, and a curry of your choice with either rice or naan. I chose the Chicken Rogan Josh and it was pretty good.

The service was extremely fast and the food was brought out within minutes. The server was also friendly and asked how the meal was.

Would come back here if I wanted a curry that's fast, affordable and good quality!

Location.Address: 157 St Albans Rd, Watford WD24 4BD, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT ATMOSPHERE AND SELECTION OF COFFEE

Viento is a super cool spot in Watford to get coffee. Theres some nice ambient music playing in the background and it's got fitting decor.

They served probably one of the best flat whites I've had in London and they had a wide coffee selection that I'd defo wanna go back for.

The muffin was great and the food served looked pretty tasty as well.

Will definitely come back here!

One thing I would change would be to add more seating. Feels quite cramped in the seating area.

Location.Address: 42 Leven St, Edinburgh EH3 9LJ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
FANTASTIC KEBABS

There are about three tables here with a couple of chairs so you can sit down but I'd say this is definitely more of a takeaway place.

I got the lamb shawarma wrap and it was really good. Decent quality meat and really tasty. I would recommend getting a sauce in the wrap cause I forgot to ask and it really would have taken the wrap to the next level.

Location.Address: 76 Thistle St, Edinburgh EH2 1EN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
TASTY DESSERTS AND GREAT ATMOSPHERE

Came here for coffee and desserts at around 2:30 on a Saturday and the place was packed. There was luckily a table available for us.

I got the sticky toffee pudding and it was amazing! The cake was soft and had a nice bite. The sauce was sweet and worked so well together with everything.

I need to go back for an actual meal cause if it was anything like dessert then its going to be awesome!

Location.Address: 6 Market St, Edinburgh EH1 1DE, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
WHAT A GREAT PLACE FOR COFFEE!

Arrived here at 10am on Sunday and managed to get seats. The baristas were super friendly to me as  I entered.

I got a flat white and an almond croissant. The croissant was perfectly sweet and crunchy! The coffee was super good as well. Theres a large selection of chocolates that needs to be tried so I definitely need to come back for them at some point.

The best part about this place is in my opinion the friendly and chill atmosphere.

Highly recommend this place! Lucy is an awesome barista!

Location.Address: 3c York Pl, Edinburgh EH1 3EB, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING COFFEE, SERVICE AND PLACE

Came here to get out of the rain on a Saturday at around 4 and was pleasently surprised with how great this place was!

I got probably one of the best flat whites that I've had in Edinburgh here and an amazing cinnamon donut! The flat white was smooth and tasty. The donut was fluffy and the perfect amount of sweetness.

The barista was awesome! Super friendly and accommodating!

Just a great place to get coffee

Location.Address: 15 Dalry Rd, Edinburgh EH11 2BQ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
NEED TO COME BACK FOR ROUND 2

I came here on a Saturday evening and managed to get a table for four people.

I got the classic beef Pho and it was pretty good. The broth was awesome and the beef was good. I need to go back here at some point to get a better range of dishes.

Location.Address: 22 High St, South Queensferry EH30 9PP, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
TASTY FOOD WITH A TASTY VIEW

We managed to get a table for four at around 1pm on Saturday and we were lucky as it started to busy just after.

They were unfortunately out of mussels so it restricted what we were able to get. Our waitress said there was a delivery happening really soon but we decided to order without that.

Decided to try the special which was a salmon linguine and it was great! The dish had a lovely creaminess to it and the sauce tasted great.

The desserts were also awesome! They were probably the best part of the meal! The profiteroles had the sweetest and tastiest cream!

There's also a nice view of the bridge if you're by the window.

Definitely coming back here!

Location.Address: 2 Sibbald Walk, Edinburgh EH8 8FT, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
SUPERB VEGITARIAN BREAKFAST AND GREAT FRENCH TOAST

Was able to grab a table for 2 at around 11am on a Sunday Morning. It was quite busy when we got there but still a few tables available.

The full English vegitarian breakfast was really good. Everything by itself was quite tasty and it all worked well together.

The french toast was surprisingly good as well. Didn't think I would enjoy such a combination of Sliced Banana, Strawberry & Raspberry Compote, Chocolate Sauce and Granola but it worked quite well!

Will come again to try more things!

Location.Address: 159-161 Bruntsfield Pl, Edinburgh EH10 4DG, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT SERVICE, GREAT PRICES AND GOOD FOOD

Had a table booked for 1:30 on a Saturday and it was much needed because it was busy when i got there.

The service here was really good as the waitresses were friendly, quick to take an order, and quick to serve food!

I got The Monty which was decent in size. Everything served was quite good however there were a few things that were not amazing. The scrambled eggs that I got were a little watery which made them lack a little taste. The potato scone was also not that fresh. The good thing about this dish is that you get a juice and coffee/tea included in the price.

I also got the pancakes with caramelized banana and  butterscotch. They were pretty nice and had a nice sweetness. They serving was the perfect amount

Location.Address: 7-11 E London St, Edinburgh EH7 4BN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
INNOVATIVE, TASTY AND FILLING

Wasn't too busy at 1pm on a Sunday so was able to get a table fairly easily. We had to wait a few minutes for the kitchen to transition from serving brunch to lunch so might wanna come here a little after 1 to avoid that wait. However the food came out quickly after we ordered it.

The Vietnamese Loaded fried were awesome! The hoisin sauce worked so well with the fries and made them extremely moreish. This provided a great combination of crunchy and sweet.

The No-Fish and Chips was super close to tasting like fish and chips and it was rather tasty as well. The banana blossom replicated the taste and texture of fish extremely well.

Highly recommend this place to anyone!

Location.Address: 9 Croall Pl, Leith Walk, Edinburgh EH7 4LT, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING FOOD, SERVICE, AND EXPERIENCE

The food and service at this place was outstanding! The resteraunt itself has quite a warm and cosy feel. I went at 12 on a Thursday and it was fairly empty and the service was very quick.

Firstly, the homemade bread was amazing! It tasted fresh and the butter was an equally tasty.

For starters I got one of the soups of the days which was a beef broth. Very flavoursome and has a nice hint of horseradish throughout to give it a little something extra.

For mains I got the Roast Pork Belly which was cooked perfectly with its crispy skin and tender meat. The bubble and squeak worked very well with the dish as well and it left me wanting more.

I finished with a sticky toffee pudding which was also fantastic. It was just the right amount of sweetness!

It was moderately priced and I will definitely go back again soon!

Location.Address: 45 N Castle St, Edinburgh EH2 3BG, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT QUALITY, TASTE AND SERVICE

Got there at opening time on a Saturday and it was pretty quiet so we got seated instantly. Along with that our service was also quick. Our server was very nice and ran through the whole menu offering suggestions on what to get.

All the decor of the resteraunt was quite well done. And there was some pleasent ambient music in the background. Overall great setting for a Japanese meal.

There was a complimentary starter which was a spring roll with a little salad and it set a great tone for the rest of the meal. There was a nice hint of wasabi in the salad dressings which gave the flavours a huge lift.

I got the seafood noodle dish and it was really good! The tastes of the prawns, noodles and vegetables meshed well together to become a great dish.

Will go again in the future!

Location.Address: 132 Morningside Rd, Edinburgh EH10 4AY, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
NICE COFFEE AND DESSERTS

I really liked this place. I came at the end of the day so the display with desserts was a little empty and I wouldn't be surprised if the really greats desserts had already been taken. However the brownie and cake that I tried were quite delicious.

As standard, you can see the picture of the cool dragon on the coffee foam. And even though it's posted like a million times and I knew exactly what to expect, it was still cool to get 😂 and my flat white was decent.

Great place to get a fairly priced cup of coffee and dessert if you're feeling it

Location.Address: 80 Bruntsfield Pl, Edinburgh EH10 4HG, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREATEST CHEESE MELTS EVER

This store has a pretty good reputation and for good reason. It's nice looking resteraunt with an open view of the park.

The service was great. The waitress was awesome and was able to help with recommendations. The food came out relatively quickly as well.

I got the BIG CHEESE and it was amazing. The bread was perfectly toasted giving the food a nice crunch and the cheese was melted to perfection. The cheese tasted great and there were other flavours that complimented that nicely.

I also got the Tatters which were really great as a side dish.

You absolutely must come here if you're wanting a great cheese melt!

Location.Address: Leith Arches, 6 Manderston St, Edinburgh EH6 8LY, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
BEST BAGELS IN EDINBURGH!

This place is really cool! It got a great aesthetic and design to the place. I think the only issue is how small the place is. Its pretty much always busy so it's always packed in the store.

I got the Chicken Parm with the everything Bagel which I think is the best to get. The chicken is tasty and has a good crisp. The marinara sauce is also awesome.

The salt Beef was pretty good as well!

Location.Address: 91 Montgomery St, Edinburgh EH7 5HZ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT PANCAKES AND SERVICE

The pancakes were definitely the best part of this meal. They were fluffy and tasty and covered in syrup. There was a lot of bacon!

The full breakfast wasn't as good as the quality of the pancakes. May have just been the one I got but the eggs were a little rubbery. Everything else was fine.

The service and atmosphere of this place is probably the best part. The owner is super nice and when I was there the people there were friendly.

Location.Address: 5 Rue Boutouil, Essaouira 44000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
DECENT FOOD WITH A GOOD SELECTION

The food here was quite good and there was a good amount of it served. I got one of the fish dishes and it was really good. Cooked well with a lot of herbs.

Be careful though. There are a lot of cats around that are really good at making you feel for them. One of the cats looked me in the eyes and started crying. Its hard not to give them some of your food.

Location.Address: Chez ali، Ouahat Sidi Brahim, Marrakesh 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
UNIQUE BUT TOURISTY

We arrived at Chez Ali and the first thing to notice is that it's quite unorganized. You're in a group and sort of filtered into different sections but you're not led by anyone.

Sat down at our table, which again was very disorganized. Some tables had two people. Other tables had six. I was hoping to get a table just with my friends as a group of 4 but we were put with a couple.

The food was completely below average. The soup was under seasoned. The lamb was stringy and tough in the Tajine. My vegitarian friend was given vegetable couscous which was like most, tasteless. The dessert was just old and dry fruit and there was some tea. Not a good meal at all!

There were dancers that danced around you're table that just looked tired. Also BEWARNED If you engage with them, they will ask you for money. Fair enough that they ask as they're probably underpaid but they were super aggressive about asking for money.

The show was quite underwhelming as well. A couple of tricks with horse riders which were not bad but it wasn't worth the trip. Everyone doing the show looked tired and worn out. Even the crowd on the night I went were over the whole performance and clapped minimally.

Overall, I paid a lot of money for a meal and show that wasnt that great. Do not recommend!!!

Location.Address: el Baqual, Boulevard el Mansour Eddahbi, 19 Bd Mohamed Zerktouni, Marrakesh 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT HOTEL - LOVELY STAFF, PRICES, AMENITIES AND LOCATION (FOR PICKUPS)

I had a good stay at the hotel. It's nothing fancy and provides everything you need.

They provide a 200dh taxi ride to and from the hotel. You are able to book excursions to the waterfalls and such for a reasonable price where you are also picked up from the hotel.

The staff are friendly and are willing to help with any reservations you need etc. The maids do a fantastic job at cleaning your room even taking time to straighten up shoes and toiletries.

The pool is clean and good for a dip but small and  there are only 8 or so chaise lounges for a hotel with a lot of people.

The breakfast is standard and filling and will get boring after the third time since the same things are served everyday. However there's a pancake and omelette station though which is awesome.

It can get quite busy at times, especially at the lifts in the morning as there can be masses of people checking in and out.

Overall the staff are nice, the hotel is located fairly centrally ( good resteraunts around the area and a 35 minute to the souk ), and you get all that you need.

Location.Address: 39 Rue Mohammed el Beqal, Marrakech 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT CHEAP BURGERS

You can grab some really great burgers from here. I got the highly recommended KechBurger and it was awesome. Everything in the burger worked together.

The chips were nice and crispy. I personally wasn't a fan of the coleslaw as it was a bit sweet for me.

Another great thing was the smoothie which was very tasty and was refreshing!

The burger, fries and coleslaw were only 55 DH which is cheap for a meal that fills you up perfectly.

Location.Address: J2G6+6WC, Marrakesh 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
NICE VIEWS AND DECENT SERVICE

It was quite difficult to know where to go to eat and where to get a good view. We stumbled across this place and were seated immediately.

From the terrace you can get a nice view of the square if you're seated close to the edge.

The foods pretty standard. I got the Tajine menu which was a set course of Moroccan Salad, Chicken Tajine and Mint tea for 65Dh. The salad was fairly fresh and simple. The chicken Tajine was alright

The service was kinda slow and we had to get someone's attention for both ordering, cleaning our table, and the check. The guy collecting the payment had the cheek to ask for a tip...

Location.Address: أوزود، Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
GOOD FOOD FOR A GOOD PRICE

This was a nice stop after having visited the Ouzoud waterfall.

I had a meal that came to 100dh which consisted of  Bread, salad, water, and a choice of a main. For the main I choose the chicken skewer and it was pretty good. There was a decent amount of spice and flavour. It was a good stop.

WiFi is pretty good and it's air conditioned!

Location.Address: 165 Rue Mohammed el Beqal, Marrakech 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
CHEAP AND AMAZING PIZZA

This is quite a nice spot to get some fresh and good quality pizza that's low cost.

The pizza at this place is made in a wood fire oven so it was made properly! The pizza had a crispy and crunchy crust which balanced out with the cheese and tomato topping.

The service was a little slow and I think it's because there was a new guy starting so he was just finding his feet but it didn't take away from the quality of the pizza.

Location.Address: 62 Tarik Ibn Ziad, Guéliz, Marrakech 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING FOOD, DECOR, AND SERVICE

This place looks amazing when you enter. My group got there at 8pm and it wasn't too busy but around 9pm it starts getting busy and if you want and outdoor table then you should book in advance.

The service was great! Our server was very helpful with recommendations and with helping my vegitarian friend choose dishes that were suitable for himself (which was a large portion of Thai Rice).

We got the set Tapas menu which was pretty good. Just about enough for four people to start of with and each dish was equally delicious. I got the chicken Penne which was amazing. Very tasty and full of flavours. Probably one of the tastiest things I've had in Marrakech and it wasn't even Moroccan food 😂

This is quite a pricey establishment though. One of the more expensive places I've been to but it's reflected in the quality and I highly recommend it.

Location.Address: J2J7+6C7, Marrakesh 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING VEGITARIAN FOOD

I have tried a few vegitarian dishes in Marrakech and they were all quite tasteless and uniform. None of them left you with a feeling that you had a decent meal.

This place changed that completely! I had the pastry dish (Option No 6) and it was great! Nicely seasoned and had a lot of flavours in the dish. The vegetables were cooked perfectly and still retained their unique taste whilst also mixing with the other vegetables. The potatoes were the best part as they were soft yet firm.

Great and friendly service and decently priced!

Juices were very fresh as well!!!

Location.Address: 81, Derb Nkhal, Rahba Lakdima, Marrakesh 40030, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT MINT TEA AND VIEWS

This place has good views of the top of the Medina! Its quite a varied display of rooftops and shows a lot of the character.

The service is friendly and speaks good English.

The Mint Tea was one of the nicer ones I've had in Marrakech. It had the perfect amount of sweetness  and bitterness. The iced coffee was decent as well.

Good for a chill stop.

Location.Address: 55 Bd Mohamed Zerktouni, Marrakech 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT MOROCCAN EXPERIENCE

This was recommended as a place to get lamb shoulder. I ordered it and they accepted the order. My friends food arrived and then they said that the lamb shoulder wasn't available which was quite unfortunate. I then had to order the lamb tagine with the aubergine. It was pretty good.

The lamb was tender but the aubergine didn't really add a lot to the dish and just felt unnecessary.

One of the best parts of the meal was the starter which was the pidgeon pie. It was the perfect balance between sweet and meat flavours. The crispiness added a lot of depth to the dish.

The decor of the place is probably the best part. Very well decorated.

Service was pretty good.

Location.Address: ourika alhaouz, Setti-Fatma, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
ENJOYABLE MOROCCAN FOOD

Came here after a hike up to the waterfall and expected it to be a touristy resteraunt with substandard food but to my surprise it was actually decent. Firstly it was open on Eid which was great as we were worried that there wouldn't be anything available.

I got the Chicken Tajine with Figs which was amazing. The chicken was succulent and tasty. The sauce was sweet. The figs were nice to have but they were too sweet to finish.

The food took a little bit of time to arrive but the server was nice a friendly and the prices were a little high but expected as it was a touristy place.

Location.Address: Rue Yves St Laurent, Marrakech 40090, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
BEAUTIFUL FOR PICTURES AND WALKING AROUND

The price to enter is 70 Dihram person which I'd say is a fair price.

There are a lot of places to take some really nice pictures of flowers and shrubbery. Whens it busy though the best spots such as where the long stretch of water is, is usually packed!

The cafe is quite pricey compared to the cafes outside of the Jardin Majorelle complex so is probably worth waiting for them.

Nice to visit for a peaceful and relaxing afternoon

Location.Address: JXFW+FQM, Marrakesh 40000, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT SERVICE AND MUSIC

This was a great place to just chill for a while. There's decent food (Not the best for vegitarian as they're aren't any legit vegitarian options). They give you quite a big portion when you order the burger. It was pretty good.

The shisha was quite nice as well and the drinks were alright.

Everyone was nice and friendly.

Location.Address: 1 Rue Yves Saint Laurent, Majorelle, Marrakesh, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
NICE ICE CREAM

Got some decent chocolate ice cream for 25 dirham. Refreshing place to go after walking around the Jardin Majorelle.

Location.Address: Marrakesh, Morocco

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT FOOD AND VERY FRIENDLY

First time in Marrakech and was just venturing out from the hotel when we stumbled upon this place.

The guy running the restaurant was super nice and spoke great English. Super accomodating and helpful with picking food.

The Moroccan tea was amazing and full of flavour.

I got the mixed Shawarma which was solid. Great and tasty portions of meat.  Nice bed of rice. Good and salted chips. And the salad was quite tasty as well. Perfect size for a meal that hit the spot after arriving in the country.

Fairly cheap as well 😁

Location.Address: 13 Antigua St, Edinburgh EH1 3NH, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AMAZING FOOD AND GREAT SERVICE

I've been here twice! One for the breakfast service and one for dinner and both times have been awesome!

Everything in the full Scottish breakfast is great on its own. The eggs are perfect, the bacon's the right amount of crispy, and the hash browns are outstanding! There is quite a big portion of beans though and a lack of bread.

For dinner I had the salad which was pretty good but the steak was the winner! It was nicely seasoned and very tasty! Just a really good steak!

The service was also amazing both times. The staff were attentive and friendly!

Such a great place and I highly recommend it!

Location.Address: 64 Elm Row, Leith, Edinburgh EH7 4AQ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
EXTREMELY ATTENTIVE BARBERS

I went in and they're were a few people waiting. When it was my turn the guy was extremely professional and attentive. There was another guy waiting but my dude took his time and gave me a great haircut.

Location.Address: 37 Leith St, Edinburgh EH1 3AT, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
BEST RAMEN IN EDINBURGH

I've been to a couple of places for ramen and this was probably the best one I've been to.

I got the black garlic ramen and it was extremely tasty. Full of garlic flavour, a little chilly and good noodles.

The service here was also great. It was quite busy when I went on a Thursday evening. There were few tables, and I had a group of 4. They were able to squeeze us in and they were super attentive.

Location.Address: 30 Albert St, Edinburgh EH7 5LG, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT PRICES

Got some takeaway from this joint. The aromatic duck was actually pretty good and the Singapore chow mein was decent. Standalone I wouldn't say it's amazing Chinese food but if you take the price into account then it's quite amazing.

Hope they get an online delivery system or something in the future

Location.Address: 14-15 Albert Pl, Edinburgh EH7 5HN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT FOOD AND GREAT PRICES

This is a very nice looking resteraunt that serves great Mexican food.

I had the black bean dip and guacamole which were both tasty and well made but it was quite expensive just for dip.

I had the tomato based dish for mains and it was nice. I would probably order a burrito though next time.

The waiter was super friendly and helpful with recommendations.

Location.Address: 3A Albert St, Edinburgh EH7 5HL, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
PREFECT PLACE TO GET BREAKFAST ANYTIME

The great thing about this cafe, is you are able to get breakfast all day. So for late risers who also want to enjoy a full English breakfast this is the place.

FULL ENGLISH

The full English is pretty good. More beans would have been nice but other than that it has everything required.

If you order a smoothie, be prepared to hear the crazy loud sounds from the blender. It's so loud!

properties.Draft Review Comment:
AMAZING FOOD

I'm not vegan but the friends I was with were. I was recommended this place and took them there. Genuinely, the food was awesome! I got the rice

Location.Address: 94 Hanover St, Edinburgh EH2 1DR, United Kingdom
36 Leven St, Edinburgh EH3 9LJ, United Kingdom
