properties.Review Comment:
YOU GOTTA TRY ALL THE FOOD

FOOD

Went with a pal and we got three dishes each and shared a the gyozas and the starters. The best starter hands down was the SIGNATURE CHICKEN WINGS! They were near perfection as they were tasty and crispy. Everything you would want in a wing. The RIBS were really tasty as well.

We also shared the aubergine and prawn Tiger gyozas which were great.

I loved the CHICKEN BOA at this place. It's got the right amount of spice and flavour.

SERVICE

The server was nice and friendly. He was also great with the recommendations.

ATMOSPHERE

This place is quite small and cosy. It's candle lit so it's quite aligned to be a date place.

Definitely go and get the wings. All the other food is great as well! I'm 100% going back!

properties.Draft Review Comment:
RECOMMEND SET B

Went on a Tuesday night and it wasn't too busy

Location.Address: 6-8 Salisbury Pl, Newington, Edinburgh EH9 1SH, United Kingdom
30a Chambers St, Edinburgh EH1 1HU, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Nice place to get drinks

If you're planning on getting drunk on a weekday then this place is great. It's not that busy. It will take a little bit of time to get the drink as there's usually only one person behind the counter.

Been here on a weekend and it gets packed.

The music isn't too loud so you can actually hear what people are saying to you and the atmosphere is not bad.

Location.Address: 9 Elm Row, Edinburgh EH7 4AA, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT SERVICE

FOOD

I got the bruschetta to start with which was morish and had a lot going for it even though it was quite a simple dish. Decent garlic bread and freshish tomatoes.

I also had a recommendation from the waiter to get this meat pasta. It was quite good. Very tomatoey 😁

PRICE

For the amount you get, it's a very decent price. Starter and a main for £15 but they were huge portions which if you're hungry this is the place to be!

SERVICE

My friend and I couldn't finish our meal and the waiter was roasting us which was super funny.
Really nice guy and the waitress was also friendly.
Memorable service from this place

Location.Address: 57 Elm Row, Edinburgh EH7 4AQ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT HOUMOUS

I always judge a Turkish place by their houmous. Maybe not the best way to do it but it's usually a good indicator. The houmous at this place is amazing and pretty fresh! It has mixed vegetables on the top and it comes with excellent bread. It was so good that I got two portions!

We also got the mixed meat platter for one which is in the pic. Great succulent and tasty pieces of meat with a balancing rice.

The service was quick and friendly.

Got the kunufeh for dessert which was pretty good. Not 100% what it's meant to taste like but it tasted good. It's quite a heavy dessert so try not to go overboard.

Location.Address: 102 Dalry Rd, Edinburgh EH11 2DW, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
AWESOME SEAFOOD

SERVICE

The staff are so welcoming and friendly. It genuinely has a very homey feel to it. Tight and close tables.

FOOD

We started off with the bread salad. The bread in the place is fantastic and fresh. It was a good starter.

Then we got the seafood platter which was the best seafood I've had in Edinburgh. Everything was amazing. There were prawns, mussels, and great broth. It wasn't too salty, you could still taste the essence of the seafood and it was very moreish. The broth was so good that I had to ask for more bread to have it by itself.

For mains, I got the aubergine pasta which was pretty good and then chocolate mousse for desert. All great but the seafood platter was the best.

PRICE

Quite pricey but honestly not too bad for three people however it could easily get up there with drinks which I didn't order

Location.Address: 67 Bread St, Edinburgh EH3 9AH, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
GREAT SCONES
SERVICE

The guy in there was pretty friendly and it wasn't too busy so the service was very quick. He brought everything for me at my table.

FOOD

The scones was pretty good but I'd say the jam was the real winner on the plate.
The  flat white was nice.

I'm interested in the event that's coming up called Sconefest. I think they said there would be 9 different types of scones.

Location.Address: 1 E Fountainbridge, Edinburgh EH3 9BH, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
WAIT TIME

Went on Saturday Morning. They're a trickle of people coming in but it's not too busy.

HAIRCUT

Great haircut and the lady really took her time with it all.

PRICE

Decently priced

Overall it was a great haircut and had a nice chat with the hair dresser( forgot her name 😅)

Location.Address: Comrie, Crieff PH6 2LS, United Kingdom
Flassches Yard, Edinburgh EH12 9LB, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment: This is one of the best companies ever!!!

Location.Address: 42 Queensferry St, Edinburgh EH2 4RA, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
It was just okay.

CICCGETTI SHARING BOARD

I wouldn't order the sharing plate with the chicken and the bread. It wasn't that good in my opinion. The chicken was kinda plain and it was just bread and dips. The calamari was also kinda tasteless. It wasn't bad but considering the price I would say that its not really worth it.

SPAGHETTI BOLOGNESE

I just got a classic here and again it was just alright. Not the best but it wasn't bad

SERVICE

Again the service was okay but it was a little slow at some points and the food took just a bit too long to come out but nothing terrible.

Its just your average Italian restaurant.

properties.Draft Review Comment: Overall this is a good place to go if you wanna get bagels.

Location.Address: 19 Queensferry St, Edinburgh EH2 4QW, United Kingdom
unit 5 St Andrew Square, Edinburgh EH2 2BD, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
I had a unique experience at this wagamamas. The day I went, they were introducing a new vegan dish by Gaz Oakley so it was cool meeting him. His dish was really good. I'm an avid meat eater so meatless dishes never truly satiate me but this one was really good! It was tasty and filling.

Got the firecracker as well which is always killer but I love the spice!

And a myriad of desserts. From all of them, I liked the cheesecake the best and that chocolate cake.

The starters are also amazing. Especially the chilli squid.

Didn't expect it to be so good.

Location.Address: 14 Home St, Edinburgh EH3 9LY, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
This was one of the more professional places that I've been to for electronics repair. You get what you pay for.

Although this pace is slightly more expensive than other repair shops, the service you get here is awesome. The guy here was nice and great at explaining the problem. He was straight up about the price as well.

My problem was a simple one and the turnaround was quick as well.

Location.Address: One Edinburgh Quay, 1 Fountainbridge, Edinburgh EH3 9QB, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
A great escape room in Edinburgh!

The staff were super friendly and accommodating. Very clear with instructions and making us feel welcome. Even though one of the group was late there was not pressure but that could be attributed by the fact that it was a slow day😝

We did Jungala, and it was awesome. The room made sense and everything was logical. The puzzles were great. We were stuck on some but it always ended up being something obvious that we didn't think about. We got out in an average amount of time.

Great escape room. Definitely coming back again at some point.

Location.Address: 94B Fountainbridge, Edinburgh EH3 9QA, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Went there on a Saturday during lunch time and there was quite a big queue for tables. During weekdays it's not too busy.

The service is great. All the servers are nice and attentive. They made sure you were acknowledged and gave you a table as fast as possible. It was quite nice that not all our party had to be there for us to get a table.

I got the full breakfast and it was pretty good. I'd recommend the white bread instead of the brow because the brown wasn't tasty. Everything else was quite good. Not the best breakfast I've had but it's up there for quality. Fairly priced.

I can only recommend this place for the breakfast selection. Haven't had lunch here.

Location.Address: 6 Viewforth, Port Seton, Prestonpans EH32 0DR, United Kingdom
332 Kilburn High Rd, London NW6 2QN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Best wings I've had in london at this place. I came with some friends and we ordered the Shanghai Oriental, the Jamaican me Crazy, and the Bangkok. Six wings are given in each dish so we all had 2 wings from each dish. This was awesome as we were able to try a selection of wings.

The wings were super tasty and the hot ones were fairly spicy.

The wait was a little long so either make a reservation or be prepared to wait.

Theres a lot to say about how great this place is but you should just go and find out for yourself 😁

Location.Address: 31 Lothian Rd, Edinburgh EH1 2DJ, United Kingdom
Location.Business Name: The Caley Picture House - JD Wetherspoon

properties.Review Comment:
Decent place to get drinks and food. On weekends, it will be thought to get a table because this place is pretty busy.

The food is okay for a bar and the service is quite fast.

Location.Address: Dalry Rd, Edinburgh EH11 2EF, United Kingdom
Budapest, Kacsa u. 22, 1027 Hungary

properties.Review Comment:
Great place. This is one of the more expensive resteraunts in Budapest but it's well worth it. Great food and great service

Can't remember exactly what I ordered but the staff do a great job of explaining what's on offer.

Highly recommend!!!

Location.Address: 98 W End Ln, London NW6 2LU, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Didn't get a chance to review it straight after the meal. Decent food. Some are winners but some weren't for me. You have to order the right thing.

The brunch is decent!

Service is good.

Location.Address: 3a St Andrew Square, Edinburgh EH2 2BD, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
The wait for this place is pretty long taking about 30 mins to get inside the resteraunt and then another 20-30 to go from the bar to a table. The staff are super friendly to you offering you chai and lemonade in the line. Get the chai btw.

This place has some of the best service I've seen from an establishment. It varies from place to place and for obvious reasons. But on the whole it's consistently good.

The food was really good except they ran out of cheesy toast which is one of my favourites. The other classic I get would be the Pau Bhaji which is always great. Tried the Okra fries which were pretty good.

The mains were decent which included the standard chicken tikka, garlic naan, and chili prawns. Everything was tasty, and had a decent amount of spice to it. I still haven't figured out the best dishes to order. They're good but I wouldn't order them again because I feel like there's something better.  The house dhaal is super good as well.

The chocolate pudding was great as well. Very rich though.

Definitely would go again and I want to go soon. When I got the bill I was expecting the worst but with some drinks, food and dessert the overall cost of the meal was pretty average.

Location.Address: 7 Charlotte Ln, Edinburgh EH2 4QZ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
If you check my reviews normally, if it's generally decent, I'll give the place five stars but this place was so average in everything for a dining experience that it's getting 3 stars.

I don't think there's enough staff to classify this as a resteraunt. I feel like this would be better as a whole go up to the bar to order food and drinks kinda place. Because it took a fair bit of time to get our orders, for food to be served and for the check to be given.

I ordered the nachos and lamb flatbread. The nachos were decent and had a good amount of nachos, side things and cheese. The lamb flatbread which is one of the more expensive things on the menu wasn't that good in my opinion. The lamb didn't taste of much and it kinda felt like a more expensive kebab that you'd get on a night out. The chips were the best part of my mains.

To the credit of the servers they were consistently asking if everything was okay but I'm not sure what they could have done if I said anything.

This place might be better to just get drinks at the outside bit. Won't go back for food inside.

In sunny weather this place has some great views and a decent sandy beach to hang out in.

I'm no photographer but you can get some great pictures of the sunset here.

Pretty easy to get to through public transport.

Went on a weekday and it wasn't that busy. Not sure how it fares on the weekend.
properties.Comment: No location information is available for this review

Location.Address: 6 Shandwick Pl, Edinburgh EH2 4RN, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Decent place to get burritos! It's not too busy during the weekdays but not sure about the weekends.

The burritos are filling as well which is important cause your spending a decent amount on it.
They're quite tasty and the ingredients taste fresh.

The churros were pretty good as well

Location.Address: Budapest, Vásár u. 2, 1084 Hungary

properties.Review Comment:
The food was really great here. I shared the pancakes with blueberries and the spinach omelette. Both were tasty and well made. The pancakes were fluffy and the syrup was the perfect amount of sweetness. The omelette was pretty good as well.

The service was efficient.

Location.Address: Staroměstské nám. 930/7, 110 00 Josefov, Czechia

properties.Review Comment:
This place was amazing for everything. The location was great since its really close to the town square.

For starters, I got the potato soup and tomato salad. Both were decent but nothing to write home about. The potato soup would be worth an order if you haven't tried it before.

For mains, I got the steak on a potato cake and it was awesome. The sauce worked really well with the steak. Highly recommend getting this if you go here.

Went on a weekday for lunch and it wasn't that busy. Was looking to order their specials but they don't offer them till after 3pm.

For dessert, I got the flourless chocolate cake and it was pretty good as well. Good to finish with.

Overall this place was excellent!

Location.Address: Sevastopolská 17, 101 00 Praha 10-Vršovice, Czechia

properties.Review Comment:
The food here was amazing! I got the plain cheeseburger and it was great. The meat was tender and tasty. The burger itself was well put together and the ingredients complimented each other.

The fries were the good kind which were the crispy and slender.

And I ordered a side of the lemon mayonnaise which was super good as well.

Great place and great service.

Location.Address: 8 Love Ln, Pinner HA5 3EF, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
This was a pretty great resteraunt.
The atmosphere was quite nice and the service was attentive as well.

I got garlic prawn starter and it was awesome. The only thing was that it was quite expensive and because I was sharing there wasn't too many prawns on the plate.

Location.Address: 34 Rue des Rosiers, 75004 Paris, France

properties.Review Comment:
I haven't had too many falafels in my life but I can safely say that this was probably one of the best that I've had.

I heard that this place get pretty busy, so we went at 11am just to avoid any queues and it wasn't too busy.

There's someone from the resteraunt helping out with orders so it makes it easy to know what to do.

The falafel itself was amazing. I got the special with everything including the chili sauce. Every one of the ingredients works well together and compliments one another. I wasn't the biggest fan of the bread so didn't finish that but the insides were spectacular!

Great Reubens are served here! I got the special Reuben with Salt Beef and Pastrami. It was really tasty. The meats were succulent and tender. The sauces worked well in the sandwich.

The fries were also great as they were the crispy.

The servers were attentive and the food cane out quickly. Although, it wasn't busy when I was there.

Location.Address: 43 High St, Watford WD17 2DJ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Pretty decent pizza for the price that you pay! For £7.95 I believe you can get a pizza with whatever you want on it. I went quite late on a Saturday night during Easter and it was that busy.

The staff were also very friendly and made the experience even more enjoyable!

Highly recommend this place!

Great place to view Tokyo.

Definelty recommend going as it's free.

There's a couple a gift shops up there with some okay stuff.

But the main attraction is the view which is very awesome and it's a great way to orient yourself in Tokyo if it's your first time there!

Location.Address: Japan, 〒151-0053 Tokyo, Shibuya City, Yoyogi, 2 Chome−2−1 新宿サザンテラス

properties.Review Comment:
It was super hot outside and I spotted the ice cream sandwich which then had to be gotten.

When I went inside the place everything looked really delicious and was moderately priced.

The chocolate and matcha ice cream sandwiches were pretty amazing!

Defiently recommend going on a hot day!

Location.Address: 11 Naitomachi, Shinjuku City, Tokyo 160-0014, Japan

properties.Review Comment:
What an amazingly picturesque park. You could almost hold your camera at any angle and an awesome picture could be taken.

Very clean and well worth the price of about £2! Some amazing spots in the park but don't be caught out by the fact that it closes at 4:30 which is quite early.

Probably worth a day hanging out here just to take it all in!

Location.Address: B1, Floor, 1 Chome-1-2 Nishishinjuku, Shinjuku City, Tokyo 160-0023, Japan

properties.Review Comment:
Great place to go for something that's not ramen!

One thing that's awesome about the place is that it's halal.

The staff were quite accomodating. I got the tempura set menu which was nice. The miso soup was very tasty! Overall pretty good for a meal in Japan

Location.Address: 124 Southwark St, London SE1 0SW, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
What an awesome place! The food was really good and you could get a decent amount for a good price. A great thing is that if you have a favourite you can load your plate up with that great food.

I particularly enjoyed the chili sin carne which was a nice take on a classic. And the onion rings and jalapeno poppers were great as well.

Location.Address: Bankside, London SE1 9TG, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Went to Tate Modern for the picasso exhibit and it was really well done.

Enjoyed the layout and amount of information that was given.

Highly recommend going here for any sort of trip whether it be a solo, family or friends trip!

Location.Address: 106 Hare Ln, Claygate, Esher KT10 0LZ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Really cool place. The staff are really nice. The food and drinks are decent.

Recommend going here if you're ever in the area and getting the Foley Burger

It's not to busy when I went so you can usually get a space.

Location.Address: 168 W End Ln, London NW6 1SD, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Really great food and a generally awesome selection!

Their cupcakes are always amazing as well!

Recommend getting their full English breakfast especially if you're vegetarian as it is really tasty.
Included are chickpeas which was fairly decent.

Really recommend going here if you have the chance!

Location.Address: London, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Super nice park. Very clean and well kept. A lot of open spaces and great for frisbee or football.

There are plenty of places to explore as there are tons of trees and fields to walk around.

There's also a really nice view of london.

properties.Review Comment:
Good quality marks and Spencers with a decent selection for quite a small place.

If you're going avoid going after work as it gets super packed due to all the people picking up last minute things.

properties.Review Comment:
Great place to do Shisha!

The shisha was good and decently priced for London. Recommend the rose which is quite a smooth flavour. Possibly combine it with mint or something for a little extra kick.

The food was also quite good for Edgware road standards. I got the mixed sharwma which I highly recommend and the homous was also tasty which is a good indication of the place as a whole.

I think the place could benefit from some fans as it can get quite hot with all the coals around.

Overall a solid Domino's!

Me and my friends tried but weren't successful and so wehad to buy our tickets full price. The guy was nice enough to give us a discount for our troubles.
What awesome staff.

Seats were comfortable and I could enjoy the film without andmy disturbances!

properties.Review Comment:

Location.Address: 28-29 Gerrard St, London W1D 6JW, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
I go to this place quite often because it's so good! No dim sum place in the UK has been able to be on the same level. Granted I haven't been to a ton of them but this is straight up a great place!

The staff are friendly enough and the wait for a table isn't too bad. If busy, usually accommodated within a couple of minutes.

Location.Address: Waverley Mall, 3/48 Waverley Bridge, Edinburgh EH1 1BQ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
I ordered the fruit mango tea with cherry juice balls which was amazing!

I didn't really have any idea what to order so i asked the lady who worked there and she was really nice and helpful as she helped me work out what I would have liked. I asked for something sweet and refreshing and we landed on mango and cherry which was great!

It was so good that 3 of my friends who were previously hesitant to try bubble tea because they never had it, all bought one after trying mine.

Highly recommended getting some bubble tea!

Location.Address: 14 S St Andrew St, Edinburgh EH2 2AZ, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
Great decently priced dim sum! Got around 15 dishes for 5 people and it came to £70 which is really good!

Not the best dim sum I've had but it's definitely up there in there. Think the portions could have been bigger but maybe the amount reflects the price.

The service was perfect and the food came quickly. Definelty recommend!

Location.Address: 112 Hanover St, Edinburgh EH2 1DR, United Kingdom

properties.Review Comment:
A great pub that is just straight up good.

The staff were friendly when I went which was around lunchtime. They were helpful when ordering and quick to make the drinks. The pitcher which I git was good value for money. Got more out of that than the single drinks.

It wasn't too busy at Saturday lunchtime so there were lenty of seats available.

I highly recommend the Ultimate Burger which is filled with Chicken, a Burger, Onion rings and comes with fries! Really delicious and filling!

Overall a really great place!

Definelty recommend! 😁
